title: PPPP’s Jamil Ahmed wins PS-11 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Jamil Ahmed has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-11, Larkana-II by securing 41,158 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Kazim Ali Khan of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 20,807 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 36.55%.
